jbb.engine
Class Board

java.lang.Object
  jbb.engine.Board
Direct Known Subclasses:
MouseLand, PacWorld
public abstract class Board
extends java.lang.Object

This abstract class contains a two-dimensional array of Tiles, that comprises the playing field of a game, as well as a two-dimensional array that contains the map of set items. It handles an individual turn of the game. The class will be extended by game-specific board classes, which will implement the populatePlayingField()method to populate the board as required by the game.

Author:
Boris Ionine, Jonathan Gravel

resetPlayingField

public abstract void resetPlayingField()
This is called when the collidesWith method declares a reset is required. For example: when a Ghost collides with PacMan or vice versa, all characters are reset to there original positions. This method simply modifies the moveableTiles list, giving the Avatars their original positions.
